    {
      "lineNumber": 4,
      "text": "DATE: 3/1/48",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 5,
      "text": "FROM : [REDACTED]",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 6,
      "text": "SUBJECT: FLYING DISCS",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 7,
      "text": "SECURITY MATTER - X",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 8,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 9,
      "text": "Reference is made to a memorandum to you from Mr. [REDACTED]",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 10,
      "text": "in the above-captioned matter dated February 19, 1948. The memorandum",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 11,
      "text": "indicated that the San Francisco Field Division had received a letter from",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 12,
      "text": "the headquarters of the Air Defense Command, Mitchel Air Force Base, New York, 67q",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 13,
      "text": "dated February 4, 1948, entitled, \"Investigation and Reporting of 'Flying Disc",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 14,
      "text": "Incidents.\" This communication indicated that investigations should be",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 15,
      "text": "coordinated with the FBI.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 16,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 17,
      "text": "The Agent in Charge of the San Francisco Field Division inquired as 11c",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 18,
      "text": "to a change in policy regarding the investigation of flying discs. A letter 113",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 19,
      "text": "was forwarded to San Francisco advising them that there had been no change in",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 20,
      "text": "the Bureau's policy. This matter has been discussed by Special Agent [REDACTED] 67C",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 21,
      "text": "of the Liaison Section with Lieutenant Colonel [REDACTED] of the",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 22,
      "text": "Intelligence Division of the Air Force. Colonel [REDACTED] advised Mr. [REDACTED]",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 23,
      "text": "that apparently the Air Defense Command at Mitchel Field was not aware of the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 24,
      "text": "fact that the Bureau was no longer conducting investigations regarding flying",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 25,
      "text": "discs. He stated that he would take the necessary action and straighten out",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 26,
      "text": "the Air Defense Command as to the present policy regarding incidents of",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 27,
      "text": "flying discs.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
